Phase 2 — Identity self-service & admin account management
Service: identity-service · PostgreSQL `identity` db

Builds on Phase 1's accounts table — no schema change, only new endpoints
against rows that already exist. Order-service and catalog-service still
have no dependency on this phase; it's sequenced here (before catalog/order)
because admin-only write endpoints in Phase 3/4 need ACC-008/009's
deactivate/reactivate/promote actions to exist for realistic testing —
e.g. verifying a Deactivated admin can't create a product.

Scenarios covered: 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9.

---

## GET /api/users/me

Scenario 4. ACC-011: a Customer can view their own profile.

Request:
```json
GET /api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer <jwt for Alice>
```

Response — 200 OK:
```json
{
  "id": "aaaaaaaa-aaaa-4aaa-8aaa-aaaaaaaaaaaa",
  "email": "alice.nguyen@example.test",
  "fullName": "Alice Nguyen",
  "role": "CUSTOMER",
  "status": "ACTIVE",
  "createdAt": "2026-07-13T09:00:00Z"
}
```

