## GET /api/users/{id}  (admin only)

Scenario 6. ACC-011: an Administrator can view any account for support.
A Customer calling this for anyone but themselves is rejected — that's
scenario 4's endpoint (/me), not this one.

Request:
```json
GET /api/users/cccccccc-cccc-4ccc-8ccc-cccccccccccc
Authorization: Bearer <jwt for admin>
```

Response — 200 OK:
```json
{
  "id": "cccccccc-cccc-4ccc-8ccc-cccccccccccc",
  "email": "chen.park@example.test",
  "fullName": "Chen Park",
  "role": "CUSTOMER",
  "status": "ACTIVE",
  "createdAt": "2026-07-13T09:05:00Z"
}
```

Response — 403 Forbidden (a Customer calling this for another account):
```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "FORBIDDEN",
    "message": "You can only view your own account."
  }
}
```

