## PATCH /api/users/{id}/role  (admin only)

Scenario 9. ACC-009: only an existing Administrator can promote another
account to Administrator — no self-service path.

Request:
```json
PATCH /api/users/cccccccc-cccc-4ccc-8ccc-cccccccccccc/role
Authorization: Bearer <jwt for admin>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "role": "ADMIN"
}
```

`ADMIN` here matches the `roles.code` value actually seeded by the
database (Archive/Development/Database §1.1) — not "ADMINISTRATOR," the
business-rules prose term for the same role (BUSINESS_RULES.md §2). This
doc used "ADMINISTRATOR" until the identity-service Phase-1 implementation
caught the mismatch against the real schema; fixed here to match the
schema, which is the actual wire-level contract.

Response — 200 OK:
```json
{
  "id": "cccccccc-cccc-4ccc-8ccc-cccccccccccc",
  "role": "ADMIN",
  "updatedAt": "2026-07-13T12:00:00Z"
}
```

Response — 403 Forbidden (anyone other than an existing Administrator
calling this, including the account calling it on itself):
```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "FORBIDDEN",
    "message": "Only an Administrator can grant the Administrator role."
  }
}
```

